{"title":"How well does bar exam performance predict subsequent success as a lawyer?","link":"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/907759946/0/marginalrevolution~How-well-does-bar-exam-performance-predict-subsequent-success-as-a-lawyer.html","date":1731398179000,"content":"<p>Eh:</p>\r\n<blockquote><p>How well does bar exam performance predict lawyering effectiveness? Is performance on some components of the bar exam more predictive? The current study, the first of its kind to measure the relationship between bar exam scores and a new lawyer’s effectiveness, evaluates these questions by combining three unique datasets—bar results from the State Bar of Nevada, a survey of recently admitted lawyers, and a survey of supervisors, peers, and judges who were asked to evaluate the effectiveness of recently-admitted lawyers. We find that performance on both the Multistate Bar Examination (MBE) and essay components of the Nevada Bar have little relationship with the assessed lawyering effectiveness of new lawyers, calling into question the usefulness of these tests.</p></blockquote>\r\n<p>Here is <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://journals.sagepub.com/doi/full/10.1177/2755323X241296683\" target=\"_blank\">the full article</a> by Jason M. Scott, Stephen N. Goggin, and David Faigman.  Via the excellent <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://www.nationalaffairs.com/blog/detail/findings-a-daily-roundup/their-party-or-yours\" target=\"_blank\">Kevin Lewis</a>.</p>\r\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://marginalrevolution.com/marginalrevolution/2024/11/how-well-does-bar-exam-performance-predict-subsequent-success-as-a-lawyer.html\">How well does bar exam performance predict subsequent success as a lawyer?</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://marginalrevolution.com\">Marginal REVOLUTION</a>.</p>\r\n<img heigh